modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and constructing 9p protocol messages, including decoding and encoding messages with specific wire formats. Operates on byte sequences and custom data types representing 9p operations and responses. Used to implement network communication in file system clients and servers adhering to the 9p standard.

Provides operations to manage and manipulate communication protocol headers, including setting and retrieving message types, tags, and payload strings. Works with mutable state for integer-based message identifiers and string-based messages. Used to construct and inspect network request metadata in low-level system calls.

This module handles file and directory access control through mode flags, enabling operations like setting permissions (read, write, execute) and managing file system interactions via low-level I/O primitives. It works with types such as file identifiers, I/O channels, and session objects to facilitate tasks like opening, reading, writing, and removing files. Specific use cases include configuring access rights for secure file operations and manipulating file descriptors for direct system-level interactions.
